Unmodified and modified protein molecules and their corresponding nucleic acid molecules providing herbicide tolerances to one or more of these herbicides are well known in the art. They are exemplified below and are incorporated herein by reference:
a) sequences encoding tolerance to glyphosate include 5-enolpyruvylshikimate-3-phosphate synthases (EPSPS;  U.S. Patent 5,627,061 ,  U.S. Patent RE39,247 ,  U.S. Patent 6,040,497 ,  U.S. Patent 5,094,945 ,  WO04074443 , and  WO04009761 ), glyphosate oxidoreductase (GOX;  U.S. Patent 5,463,175 ), glyphosate decarboxylase ( WO05003362  and  U.S. Patent Application 20040177399 ), and glyphosate-N-acetyl transferase (GAT;  U.S. Patent publication 20030083480 ) conferring tolerance to glyphosate;
